29/11/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police announced on Tuesday (November 28th) the arrests of two men, suspected of trying to plant a bomb on a ferry linking the Adriatic port city of Zadar with Ancona in Italy. 
Officers allegedly found plastic explosives on one of the suspects. 
Zadar police chief Anton Drazina said the blast would have had "huge consequences", given the bustling location. 
(Financial Times - 29/11/06; Reuters - 28/11/06)
